Bose Ransome-Kuti, wife of late human rights activist, Beko Ransome-Kuti is dead. She died last night at the age of 74 years, PM news reports. It was learnt that Bose died of complications from brain surgery, at a hospital in Lagos. Until her death, she was the Chief Executive Officer of Boselli Ventures Limited, Anthony area of Lagos. She also attended Yejide Girls Grammar School, Ibadan, Oyo State and Pitmans College, London. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.